        {
          "username": "Cora",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "100441879788119055928",
          "user_review_count": 7,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLp3WnHTZRwhX0boQQ3vGoTEL9PqwTYqajrlsFy_SdslA4E3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I was able to schedule hours ahead - was seen ASAP when I got there - was given radiology and a brace - my insurance went seamlessly through, I didnt even have a copay for the first time since CityMD showed up. Im grateful theres much needed urgent care competition available - Im never looking back and only coming to MedRite from now on. Already recommended to my friends to go to MedRite facilities.\n\nCommendations to the doctor and nurse who took care of me - your bedside manner, gentle and empathetic care, and expediency and communication make you both an absolute credit to the healthcare industry.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tWclZIQjZNamxSUVc1a2FsUkRWMVZsZDNCQ1gyYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x96d01be4b88995db!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkVrVHB6MjlRQW5kalRDV1Vld3BCX2c%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-02-06T16:19:23+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Abi V",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "115946598208463291692",
          "user_review_count": 15,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLYv4RM5In1mOkenCaJl4bEHqbh9O2_IurZytq0vzPM6g5yPw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Two of us arrived for a scheduled appointment and waited over two hours to be seen. During that time i requested ETA for the tech and was continuously given incorrect estimates about when the X-ray tech would arrive. Eventually they got the manager on the phone and she explained that whether you walk in or make an appointment,\nImaging services depend entirely on when the technician shows up\u2026meaning patients are expected to wait indefinitely.\n\nThis reflects a serious lack of coordination and consideration for patients\u2019 time. If imaging staff are unavailable or delayed, patients should be notified in advance and given an accurate expectation of wait times so they can make informed decisions. The tech arrived and was very pleasant and professional and the test was done in less than 5mis as expected.\n\nIt is 2026, there is no excuses for this level of poor communication and planning at Medrite. Patients deserve transparency, respect, and better operational coordination. Please\nDo better for your patients.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tsVU9FZDVSM0ZhTXpWc1pVWnFXazh6U2xORlNYYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x96d01be4b88995db!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOklUOEd5R3FaMzVsZUZqWk8zSlNFSXc%7C%7C?hl=en",
